title: Highest Regulatory Quality
description: In 2023, Australia achieved a perfect score of 100 in the Regulatory Quality percentile rank, indicating the highest regulatory quality worldwide.

title: Highest Preprimary School Enrollment
description: In 2020, Australia's gross enrollment rate for preprimary education reached 160.2%, the highest in the world, with male enrollment at 163.3% and female enrollment at 156.9%.

title: Lowest Battle-related Deaths
description: In 2018, Australia recorded only 1 battle-related death, one of the lowest numbers globally, reflecting its peaceful status.

title: High Prevalence of Overweight Children
description: In 2024, 26.4% of children under 5 in Australia were estimated to be overweight, one of the highest rates globally.
